The paper deals with the problem of drawing planar graphs with a prescribed convex polygon as the outer face, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The authors also mention the use of data structures to efficiently compute the drawings (cs.DS). The paper involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.GT and cs.DM. Finally, the authors mention the potential applications of their method in information visualization (cs.SI).
